# Testing Best Practices

**Test:**

- User-facing behavior (UI, interactions)
- Business logic & data transformations
- Error handling & edge cases
- Loading & success states

**Don't test:**

- Internal implementation (hooks, internal state)
- Third-party libraries (React Query, Zod)
- Trivial code (getters, one-liners)

**Patterns:**

- Descriptive names: `test('displays error when login fails')`
- Always test loading & error states
- Mock APIs & libraries
- Factory functions for test data
- Tests must be independent & runnable in any order
